comments: Fox (SAC) brings his arm toward George's (LAC) path and marginal contact occurs during George's drive.
Fox (SAC) legally contests George's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAC) places his forearm to Fox's (SAC) front and marginal contact occurs during Fox's drive.
Westbrook (LAC) initiates contact to Fox's (SAC) wrist and causes him to lose control of the ball.
Fox (SAC) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds and LAC should have been given possession.
Covington (LAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Covington (LAC) contests Huerter's (SAC) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Fox (SAC) grabs Westbrook's (LAC) arm prior to his gather and the contact affects his SQBR.  The contact should be deemed a non-shooting foul.
Westbrook (LAC) makes contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Fox (SAC) prior to incidental arm contact occurring at the end of the drive.
Batum (LAC) makes contact with the ball and slides his hand off prior to any incidental contact occurring.
Batum (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Sabonis (SAC) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Covington (LAC) makes contact with the ball initially and as the ball is getting lose Covington lightly brushes Sabonis' (SAC) hand.
Batum (LAC) avoids stepping out of bounds while still in possession of the ball.
Fox (SAC) and George (LAC) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball in the post.
Fox (SAC) moves along George's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs as he releases his pass.
Batum (LAC) brings his arm toward Monk's (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs during Monk's drive.
Batum (LAC) brushes Sabonis' (SAC) arm and marginal contact occurs during Sabonis'  shot attempt near the rim.
Covington (LAC) establishes himself in Barnes's (SAC) path and slightly extends his arms as they disengage.
Barnes (SAC) is moving alongside George's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs during George's drive.
Barnes (SAC) jumps alongside George's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Covington (LAC) places his hands to Lyles' (SAC) side and marginal body contact occurs as he slides his hands off in pursuit of the loose ball.
Mitchell (SAC) places his arm to George's (LAC) side and marginal body contact occurs as they come together in transition.
LAC does not establish the ball in the frontcourt within 8 seconds.
